Refers to the subunits that constitute the inner rings of the proteasome core complex, as in, but not restricted to, the eukaryotes (Eukaryota, ncbi_taxonomy_id:2759).
Refers to the subunits that constitute the inner rings of the proteasome core complex as seen in eukaryotes.

The beta-subunit segment of the 20S core proteosome. The 20S core proteosome is a barrel-shaped structure which consists of four 'rings', two outer, two inner, each containing seven subunits. The beta-subunits form the two inner rings.
